1
00:00:23,900 --> 00:00:25,590
Please.

2
00:01:40,510 --> 00:01:43,510
Your results are in, Ms. Monou.

3
00:01:43,510 --> 00:01:46,420
According to our diagnosis,

4
00:01:46,420 --> 00:01:48,980
you are infertile.

5
00:01:50,540 --> 00:01:56,490
A natural pregnancy
will be near impossible for your body.

6
00:01:56,490 --> 00:01:59,100
Even if you undergo a corrective procedure,

7
00:01:59,100 --> 00:02:04,980
you would only be 10% more likely
to become pregnant.

8
00:02:07,170 --> 00:02:11,120
I'm... infertile?

9
00:02:11,120 --> 00:02:14,240
Ms. Monou.

10
00:02:14,240 --> 00:02:18,150
Though your chances are low,
they are not zero.

11
00:02:18,150 --> 00:02:21,260
I advise you to discuss solutions

12
00:02:21,260 --> 00:02:24,800
with your fiancé as soon as possible,

13
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:27,220
and come visit our clinic again.

14
00:02:28,140 --> 00:02:30,120
I'm...

15
00:02:31,130 --> 00:02:32,800
Infertile.

16
00:02:40,210 --> 00:02:41,840
I'm sorry.

17
00:02:48,080 --> 00:02:50,740
I wanted to stay with you forever, Sui.

18
00:02:52,300 --> 00:02:54,510
But when my parents saw your records...

19
00:02:54,510 --> 00:02:55,450
[Diagnosis]

20
00:02:55,450 --> 00:02:58,120
They told me the marriage was off.

21
00:03:02,280 --> 00:03:04,820
I want to marry you, Sui.

22
00:03:04,820 --> 00:03:07,450
I don't care about your status or family.

23
00:03:07,450 --> 00:03:10,820
Don't worry, I'll get my parents to understand.

24
00:03:10,820 --> 00:03:12,770
Satoshi...

25
00:03:14,130 --> 00:03:17,900
But to help put my parents at ease,

26
00:03:17,900 --> 00:03:20,710
could I ask you to get a check-up first?

27
00:03:26,690 --> 00:03:30,550
I couldn't do anything more for you, okay?

28
00:03:31,510 --> 00:03:35,620
I mean, infertile? After seven years together?

29
00:03:38,570 --> 00:03:40,720
Damn it!

30
00:03:51,750 --> 00:03:55,620
- Congratulations!
- You're next!

31
00:03:55,620 --> 00:03:57,940
I wanted the bouquet...

32
00:03:57,940 --> 00:04:00,270
Thank you.

33
00:04:04,290 --> 00:04:05,550
Here.

34
00:04:05,550 --> 00:04:07,750
Flowers for my dear older sister.

35
00:04:07,750 --> 00:04:09,550
- For me?
- Yup.

36
00:04:09,550 --> 00:04:11,480
A little happiness, from me to you.

37
00:04:11,480 --> 00:04:13,540
Next it's your turn, okay?

38
00:04:16,380 --> 00:04:18,170
Thanks.

39
00:04:22,210 --> 00:04:28,170
Sui, thank you for raising me
in place of our parents.

40
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:31,450
Rin...

41
00:04:32,670 --> 00:04:37,120
I was surprised to hear
you broke up with your fiancé.

42
00:04:37,120 --> 00:04:39,440
But...

43
00:04:39,440 --> 00:04:43,530
I know you'll find someone better, and fast.

44
00:04:44,200 --> 00:04:46,040
I'll always be rooting for you.

45
00:04:46,040 --> 00:04:47,900
Thanks.

46
00:04:51,440 --> 00:04:56,480
Let's make sure our kids
become best friends, okay?

47
00:05:04,900 --> 00:05:08,720
I'm going to inherit this company.

48
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:12,920
Of course I had to break up
with someone infertile.

49
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:16,300
What? Sui is infertile?

50
00:05:16,300 --> 00:05:18,370
No wonder you ended things

51
00:05:18,370 --> 00:05:22,070
with the girl you were crazy for.

52
00:05:22,070 --> 00:05:24,430
Guess it can't be helped if she's infertile.

53
00:05:24,430 --> 00:05:26,700
She wouldn't get you an heir.

54
00:05:26,700 --> 00:05:29,610
But you didn't have to fire her, did you?

55
00:05:29,610 --> 00:05:31,270
I didn't fire her.

56
00:05:31,270 --> 00:05:32,940
Mom said...

57
00:05:36,870 --> 00:05:38,360
I mean.

58
00:05:39,280 --> 00:05:41,890
My parents said she was better off elsewhere.

59
00:05:43,580 --> 00:05:46,100
Sui's probably awkward here anyway.

60
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:48,710
But hey, if she's infertile,

61
00:05:48,710 --> 00:05:53,270
doesn't that mean you two can do it raw?

62
00:05:53,270 --> 00:05:57,040
That's a big win!

63
00:06:06,490 --> 00:06:08,830
Sui.

64
00:06:11,800 --> 00:06:13,490
Honestly, Sui.

65
00:06:13,490 --> 00:06:18,060
Don't listen to their vile words.

66
00:06:18,060 --> 00:06:19,230
Takizawa...

67
00:06:19,230 --> 00:06:23,040
They're practically saying
you've failed as a woman.

68
00:06:23,040 --> 00:06:26,330
- What?
- Unforgivable.

69
00:06:28,530 --> 00:06:31,880
Failed, as a woman.

70
00:06:33,890 --> 00:06:35,620
Did you say something?

71
00:06:35,620 --> 00:06:38,400
No, not at all.

72
00:06:39,960 --> 00:06:43,140
I'm planning your farewell party,

73
00:06:43,140 --> 00:06:46,950
so look forward to it, okay?

74
00:06:46,950 --> 00:06:48,620
Thank you.

75
00:06:48,620 --> 00:06:50,910
Aw, this is nothing.

76
00:06:50,910 --> 00:06:53,850
Especially given how much you've done for me.

77
00:06:53,850 --> 00:06:57,820
I'll make sure we send you off with a blast.

78
00:06:57,820 --> 00:06:59,530
Thanks.

79
00:06:59,530 --> 00:07:04,280
Let's enjoy these last few days together!

80
00:07:17,630 --> 00:07:19,930
[Monou]

81
00:07:35,110 --> 00:07:38,640
To Rin's marriage,
and your graduation from parent status.

82
00:07:38,640 --> 00:07:40,540
Cheers!

83
00:07:46,890 --> 00:07:50,260
I seriously have to give it to you.

84
00:07:50,260 --> 00:07:52,410
Not everyone can put themselves second,

85
00:07:52,410 --> 00:07:57,420
and send their sister to college
after their parents passed.

86
00:07:57,420 --> 00:08:02,030
To think a crybaby like her
is now going to become a mother.

87
00:08:02,790 --> 00:08:05,920
You won't have to look after Rin anymore.

88
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:08,460
So, you'd better start focusing on yourself.

89
00:08:08,460 --> 00:08:09,740
Erika...

90
00:08:09,740 --> 00:08:11,330
So, what's the plan now?

91
00:08:11,330 --> 00:08:15,050
You're quitting the job,
and letting your sister have the house.

92
00:08:15,050 --> 00:08:17,510
Yeah. Rin's family will only grow,

93
00:08:17,510 --> 00:08:21,770
so a single house is far too much for me.

94
00:08:21,770 --> 00:08:26,260
And I'll find a new job,
as long as I'm not choosy.

95
00:08:26,260 --> 00:08:28,810
Want me to introduce you
to my father's company?

96
00:08:28,810 --> 00:08:31,510
It's a similar sort of real estate job,

97
00:08:31,510 --> 00:08:34,720
and they have employee housing, too.

98
00:08:34,720 --> 00:08:38,920
Thanks, but I assume positions
will be scarce anyway.

99
00:08:38,920 --> 00:08:41,660
I suppose you're right.

100
00:08:41,660 --> 00:08:46,820
Maybe this was for the better.

101
00:08:46,820 --> 00:08:48,510
What do you mean?

102
00:08:49,400 --> 00:08:54,440
Finding out about my infertility
after marriage would've been worse.

103
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:56,670
So, in a way,

104
00:08:56,670 --> 00:09:00,850
I think his rejection was in good faith.

105
00:09:01,720 --> 00:09:03,120
It was not.

106
00:09:03,120 --> 00:09:04,980
Himukai's a scumbag.

107
00:09:04,980 --> 00:09:07,290
Don't listen to that bastard.

108
00:09:07,290 --> 00:09:09,220
You dummy. Goody-two-shoes.

109
00:09:09,220 --> 00:09:12,110
- Erika, that's enough about him.
- Oh, I'm not done.

110
00:09:12,110 --> 00:09:14,070
He's pathetic. A momma's boy.

111
00:09:14,070 --> 00:09:15,520
A rich guy with no spine.

112
00:09:15,520 --> 00:09:17,320
I promise, I'm fine now.

113
00:09:17,320 --> 00:09:19,720
- There you go again.
- Huh?

114
00:09:19,720 --> 00:09:22,060
It's a bad habit of yours.

115
00:09:22,060 --> 00:09:26,290
You tend to hold back on yourself.

116
00:09:26,290 --> 00:09:30,040
You're allowed to complain
and rely on others, okay?

117
00:09:30,040 --> 00:09:34,080
Your friends and loved ones
will always be happy to listen.

118
00:09:36,560 --> 00:09:41,010
Then could I say just one thing?

119
00:09:41,010 --> 00:09:43,080
Lay it on me.

120
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:45,280
When my marriage was called off,

121
00:09:45,280 --> 00:09:49,750
rumors about my body circulated the office.

122
00:09:49,750 --> 00:09:52,010
- What?
- That's one thing.

123
00:09:52,010 --> 00:09:54,340
That was a shocker in it of itself.

124
00:09:54,340 --> 00:09:58,610
But then, a junior of mine said...

125
00:09:58,610 --> 00:10:03,390
<i>They're practically saying
you've failed as a woman.</i>

126
00:10:03,390 --> 00:10:06,210
<i>Unforgivable.</i>

127
00:10:06,960 --> 00:10:12,720
Those words really shook me.

128
00:10:12,720 --> 00:10:15,200
Who the hell said that about you?

129
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:18,870
- I won't forgive her.
- No, I swear she's a nice girl.

130
00:10:18,870 --> 00:10:20,820
She just happened to make a biting remark.

131
00:10:20,820 --> 00:10:24,260
Still, that's nothing to say to...

132
00:10:24,260 --> 00:10:25,910
Hold on.

133
00:10:26,980 --> 00:10:28,620
[Misaki Takizawa]

134
00:10:28,620 --> 00:10:30,780
[How does this restaurant sound?]

135
00:10:32,610 --> 00:10:34,330
What's up?

136
00:10:36,430 --> 00:10:39,110
My department's holding

137
00:10:39,110 --> 00:10:42,940
a farewell party for me next Friday.

138
00:10:44,720 --> 00:10:47,810
[Palace of Versailles]

139
00:10:51,700 --> 00:10:53,610
Do you have any more?

140
00:10:55,610 --> 00:11:00,260
I'm so glad we could have dinner

141
00:11:00,260 --> 00:11:03,560
at one of your favorite restaurants, Sui.

142
00:11:03,560 --> 00:11:08,000
I've never been somewhere so fancy.
You've got great taste.

143
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:11,060
Great restaurant choice, Takizawa.

144
00:11:11,060 --> 00:11:13,200
Thank you.

145
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:17,610
I wanted Sui to have one last
great memory with us here.

146
00:11:19,250 --> 00:11:21,350
What dish would you recommend?

147
00:11:21,350 --> 00:11:22,780
Huh?

148
00:11:23,480 --> 00:11:25,010
<i>The tripe's great here.</i>

149
00:11:25,010 --> 00:11:27,450
It's one of their specialties.

150
00:11:27,450 --> 00:11:30,520
"Tripe"? I've never had it before.

151
00:11:30,520 --> 00:11:31,620
You haven't?

152
00:11:31,620 --> 00:11:34,010
Score! A first for me!

153
00:11:34,010 --> 00:11:37,490
Then tripe will be a memorable dish for us.

154
00:11:37,490 --> 00:11:39,050
Yeah.

155
00:11:45,150 --> 00:11:49,490
Looks like this place specializes in tripe.

156
00:11:49,490 --> 00:11:52,760
Let's definitely order some of that.

157
00:11:56,210 --> 00:11:58,690
I'd recommend their other dishes as well.

158
00:11:59,930 --> 00:12:01,620
Like what?

159
00:12:01,620 --> 00:12:04,870
The escargot, and potatoes are great, too.

160
00:12:05,520 --> 00:12:07,130
- Everyone have a glass?
- Yes, sir.

161
00:12:07,130 --> 00:12:11,280
Here's to Monou's bright future. Cheers!

162
00:12:11,280 --> 00:12:13,840
Cheers!

163
00:12:13,840 --> 00:12:16,170
Thank you.

164
00:12:18,180 --> 00:12:20,070
That's good.

165
00:12:20,910 --> 00:12:23,570
Have you already found another job?

166
00:12:23,570 --> 00:12:25,600
Not yet.

167
00:12:25,600 --> 00:12:31,320
I'm sure you'll find a place
to utilize your CAD skills.

168
00:12:31,320 --> 00:12:32,560
Thanks.

169
00:12:32,560 --> 00:12:36,110
I did always love looking at architecture.

170
00:12:36,110 --> 00:12:39,740
Is there anything else
you've dreamt of doing?

171
00:12:39,740 --> 00:12:40,830
Not really.

172
00:12:40,830 --> 00:12:43,100
Taking it easy isn't so bad either.

173
00:12:43,100 --> 00:12:45,940
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

174
00:12:45,940 --> 00:12:48,730
Do you have any dreams yourself, Nakano?

175
00:12:48,730 --> 00:12:52,200
I'm too busy dealing with my newborn kid.

176
00:12:52,200 --> 00:12:55,730
Can you believe my wife wants two more?

177
00:12:55,730 --> 00:12:58,950
- Kids are cute, so I understand.
- I suppose.

178
00:13:01,680 --> 00:13:04,610
Though kids aren't a necessity, of course.

179
00:13:04,610 --> 00:13:06,410
Right.

180
00:13:07,180 --> 00:13:08,660
Exactly!

181
00:13:08,660 --> 00:13:12,650
No kids, no marriage,
it's all up to the individual!

182
00:13:12,650 --> 00:13:15,330
Great point.

183
00:13:16,690 --> 00:13:19,630
Your glass is looking empty there, Sui.

184
00:13:19,630 --> 00:13:22,290
Sorry I didn't notice.

185
00:13:22,290 --> 00:13:26,130
Yes, drink up, Monou. It's your party.

186
00:13:27,240 --> 00:13:30,230
Don't be shy, eat your fill!

187
00:13:32,310 --> 00:13:33,890
How's that?

188
00:13:33,890 --> 00:13:35,190
Tastes great.

189
00:13:35,190 --> 00:13:38,360
Really?

190
00:13:38,360 --> 00:13:40,310
Thank you for all your hard work.

191
00:13:40,310 --> 00:13:43,030
- No, thank you.
- Take care.

192
00:13:43,030 --> 00:13:44,960
You sure you're not joining for round two?

193
00:13:44,960 --> 00:13:46,310
Yes.

194
00:13:46,310 --> 00:13:49,000
What a shame.

195
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:52,530
Keep in touch, okay?

196
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:55,760
Then let's mosey on to the next bar.

197
00:13:55,760 --> 00:13:57,370
- All right.
- See you, Monou.

198
00:13:57,370 --> 00:14:00,050
- Good night.
- Good luck.

199
00:14:00,050 --> 00:14:02,390
Get home safe.

200
00:14:02,390 --> 00:14:03,900
All right guys, drinks are on me!

201
00:14:03,900 --> 00:14:07,100
Yes!

202
00:14:23,890 --> 00:14:25,210
How about a drink on me?

203
00:14:25,210 --> 00:14:29,010
- No thank you.
- Aw, but you look free.

204
00:14:38,210 --> 00:14:40,730
Did you need something from my girlfriend?

205
00:14:42,810 --> 00:14:47,150
So, the uggo's got a boyfriend.

206
00:14:51,240 --> 00:14:53,220
Are you allright?

207
00:14:53,220 --> 00:14:56,360
Yes, thank you.

208
00:14:56,360 --> 00:14:58,880
You're drunk stupid.

209
00:15:00,280 --> 00:15:02,140
Where do you live?

210
00:15:03,640 --> 00:15:07,730
I don't wanna go home.

211
00:15:28,420 --> 00:15:31,060
Here, water. Drink up.

212
00:15:41,870 --> 00:15:43,660
Wait.

213
00:15:50,130 --> 00:15:51,790
Why?

214
00:15:54,050 --> 00:15:56,140
We're not doing anything?

215
00:16:07,850 --> 00:16:10,530
Don't try something you're not used to.

216
00:16:13,110 --> 00:16:14,700
<i>Sui is infertile?</i>

217
00:16:14,700 --> 00:16:16,740
<i>They're practically saying</i>

218
00:16:16,740 --> 00:16:20,390
<i>you've failed as a woman.</i>

219
00:16:30,510 --> 00:16:32,460
Don't go.

220
00:17:02,100 --> 00:17:06,190
<i>I don't care what happens anymore.</i>

221
00:17:20,390 --> 00:17:22,350
Please.

222
00:17:53,670 --> 00:17:56,880
I know this won't sound convincing, but...

223
00:18:02,300 --> 00:18:05,200
You ought to be more wary. You're a woman.

224
00:18:07,400 --> 00:18:09,270
A woman...

225
00:18:16,430 --> 00:18:18,850
Don't bother putting one on.

226
00:18:18,850 --> 00:18:20,520
You won't need to.

227
00:18:21,860 --> 00:18:25,700
I'll be fine.

228
00:18:25,700 --> 00:18:27,360
So...

229
00:18:41,920 --> 00:18:43,870
What are you talking about?

230
00:18:47,040 --> 00:18:50,280
These are for protecting your body.

231
00:19:43,100 --> 00:19:44,710
Morning.

232
00:19:47,720 --> 00:19:52,000
I'm so sorry. I was out of it yesterday.

233
00:20:01,300 --> 00:20:03,240
Feeling better?

234
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:05,930
Yup.

235
00:20:05,930 --> 00:20:07,570
Thank you.

236
00:20:07,570 --> 00:20:09,670
That's all for us.

237
00:20:09,670 --> 00:20:12,020
Good bye.

238
00:20:28,890 --> 00:20:31,260
It's fine.

239
00:20:31,260 --> 00:20:34,090
I'll stay until you sleep.

240
00:21:05,800 --> 00:21:10,270
<i>Hey! How was the party yesterday?</i>

241
00:21:10,270 --> 00:21:11,950
It was complicated.

242
00:21:11,950 --> 00:21:15,570
But it gave me the motivation to move on.

243
00:21:15,570 --> 00:21:17,290
<i>As you should.</i>

244
00:21:17,290 --> 00:21:18,940
So, here's the thing.

245
00:21:27,440 --> 00:21:32,200
Could you introduce me to that job after all?

246
00:21:32,200 --> 00:21:34,870
The one at your father's workplace.

247
00:21:35,640 --> 00:21:37,690
Yeah, I want to give it a shot.

248
00:21:38,860 --> 00:21:40,680
Thanks.

249
00:21:40,680 --> 00:21:44,850
What, really?

250
00:21:44,850 --> 00:21:46,310
[Monou]

251
00:21:46,310 --> 00:21:49,040
So, the new hire is coming in next week?

252
00:21:49,040 --> 00:21:51,580
Yup. It seems she's an old friend of Erika's.

253
00:21:51,580 --> 00:21:54,370
Hopefully your spartan work ethic
won't scare her off.

254
00:21:54,370 --> 00:21:56,730
Hey!

255
00:21:56,730 --> 00:21:58,420
Although, I am a bit worried...

256
00:21:58,420 --> 00:22:01,830
Don't be, she'll warm up to you.

257
00:22:01,830 --> 00:22:04,030
That doesn't sound reassuring.

258
00:22:05,310 --> 00:22:06,390
How do you read her name?

259
00:22:06,390 --> 00:22:08,470
It's read, "Monou".

260
00:22:08,470 --> 00:22:10,870
"Monou".

261
00:22:10,870 --> 00:22:12,460
Unusual name, isn't it?

262
00:22:12,460 --> 00:22:14,400
- You could read it?
- Not at first.

263
00:22:14,400 --> 00:22:15,930
Glad I wasn't alone.

264
00:22:20,260 --> 00:22:24,220
I didn't think you'd move out so quick.

265
00:22:24,220 --> 00:22:28,860
Erika says I'm better off not dawdling.

266
00:22:28,860 --> 00:22:32,510
I'll miss having you around.

267
00:22:32,510 --> 00:22:35,670
But that's just me being selfish.

268
00:22:35,670 --> 00:22:38,530
Don't worry, I'll come back to help often.

269
00:22:38,530 --> 00:22:40,420
Thanks.

270
00:22:41,110 --> 00:22:46,500
Still, I can't help but worry
about a lady living alone...

271
00:22:46,500 --> 00:22:48,100
I'll be fine.

272
00:22:48,100 --> 00:22:50,640
The apartment's a company dormitory,

273
00:22:50,640 --> 00:22:53,720
so my neighbor is a fellow coworker.

274
00:22:55,080 --> 00:22:58,420
Then I guess no weirdos will be around.

275
00:23:00,040 --> 00:23:02,930
Call me immediately
if you face any trouble, okay?

276
00:23:02,930 --> 00:23:06,650
And you take care of your body.

277
00:23:06,650 --> 00:23:08,690
Okay.

278
00:23:10,950 --> 00:23:13,250
- They have gotten big.
- Yeah.

279
00:23:23,410 --> 00:23:25,660
<i>Your door is now locked.</i>

280
00:23:29,570 --> 00:23:32,000
Guess that wasn't all for us, huh?

281
00:23:45,360 --> 00:23:47,940
What do you think of the night we shared?

282
00:23:47,940 --> 00:23:50,660
He's being extra kind to her.

283
00:23:50,660 --> 00:23:52,870
Good night.

284
00:23:52,870 --> 00:23:56,200
You haven't given up
on your own happiness, right?

285
00:23:56,200 --> 00:23:57,500
Why are you...

286
00:23:57,500 --> 00:23:59,700
I can't give up on you, Sui.

